on":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":28,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705206,"age":30,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Anne Lynford was born in 1541, in Exeter, Devon, England as the daughter of William John Lynford. She married Sir Robert Smythe Of Highgate about 1557, in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died on 23 September 1579, in Devon, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 38, and was buried in London, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1541–23 Sep 1579":"1541–23. september 1579","1541–1579":"1541–1579","1541–1593":"1541–1593","1579–1677":"1579–1677","1510–1574":"1510–1574","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1579":"1579","1677":"1677","1510":"1510","1541":"1541","1574":"1574","1571":"1571","1593":"1593","ABT 1557":"umbes 1557","23 Sep 1579":"23. september 1579","1549":"1549","of, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Exeter, Devon, England":"Exeter, Devon, England","Newport Pagnell, Milton Keynes Borough, Buckinghamshire, England":"Newport Pagnell, Buckinghamshire, England","London, England":"London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1541–23 Sep 1579":"1541–23. syyskuuta 1579","1541–1579":"1541–1579","1541–1593":"1541–1593","1579–1677":"1579–1677","1510–1574":"1510–1574","1569":"1569","155